<div class="row mar-top-neg-20 pad-bot-5">
  <div class="col-md-8">
     <div class="header-text">This site is designed to help you meet the <strong>Title 24 Compliance</strong> in California. <%= link_to "Create an account", new_user_registration_path %> and follow the workflow to create a building model using simplified geometry inputs.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4 green-border">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-1">
        <div class="row pad-bot-10">
          <% if can? :create, Project %>
            <%= link_to "Open an Existing Project", user_path(current_user), class: "btn btn-success col-md-10" %>
          <% else %>
            <%= link_to "Open an Existing Project", new_user_session_path, class: "btn btn-success col-md-10"%>
          <% end %>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <%= link_to "Start a New Project", wizard_path, class: "btn btn-success col-md-10" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-2"><a href="http://nrel.github.io/t24_compliance_help/" target="_blank"><%= image_tag 'icon_help.png', alt: 'Help' %></a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row pad-top-20 pad-sides-sm">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <%= image_tag 'project-workflow.png', alt: 'Description of workflow for Title 24 Compliance', class: 'project-workflow-text' %>
    <%= image_tag 'bg.jpg', class: 'full-width project-workflow-bg' %>
    <div class="off-screen">
      <h3>Project Workflow</h3>
      <p>You can travel back and forth in this workflow and continue editing your model. Save the model before moving to a new section. Return to your account page later to open the model and complete the fields.</p>
      <ol>
        <li><h4>Project</h4> Add the project information including the <strong>location, team members,</strong> and <strong>exceptions</strong>.</li>
        <li><h4>Building</h4> Enter the total square <strong>footage</strong> of your building and add <strong>stories</strong>.</li>
        <li><h4>Constructions</h4> Define <strong>default constructions</strong> for your building. These will be applied to the spaces as you make them, but you can later edit them at an individual surface level.</li>
        <li><h4>Spaces</h4> Add spaces to your model. Then refine and edit the spaces in a table view. In this section you will set <strong>surfaces, subsurfaces, constructions, space functions, lighting, process loads, natural gas usage,</strong> and <strong>other settings</strong> for each space.</li>
        <li><h4>Systems</h4> <strong>Add air and zone systems</strong> and edit the settings on the components. The <strong>fluid systems</strong> needed to support the air systems will be added automatically. Customize the settings on the fluid systems by editing the components.</li>
        <li><h4>Zones</h4> <strong>Create thermal zones,</strong> assign your spaces to zones, attach systems, define the settings on the exhaust systems, and connect terminal units.</li>
        <li><h4>Check</h4> <strong>Run a compliance check</strong> and view the results.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
